{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7b43c9e6-f090-456d-837a-c2524e36b6a9","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\n`dotnet test --filter` uses VSTest syntax (`&`, `~`). MTP uses `--filter` on the **executable itself** with a different syntax. With `dotnet test` and MTP enabled, pass the filter via `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n| VSTest | MTP (xUnit v3) |\n|--------|----------------|\n| `&` | `and` |\n| `\\|` | `or` |\n| `~` (contains) | `~` (still works) |\n| `=` (exact) | `=` (still works) |\n\n### 2. Trait filtering\n\nxUnit v3 maps `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` so `Category=Smoke` continues to work as a filter property.\n\n### Your CI command becomes:\n\n```bash\n# MTP-style (recommended with UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true)\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe `--` separator tells `dotnet test` to forward the remaining args to the MTP test host. The boolean operator changes from `&` to `and`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c4888dcd-bed6-4071-82d6-39c7c15f1bdb","outputTokens":327,"requestId":"4811:301230:3128DB4:35D09B8:69FBE4B4"},"id":"79c58595-cb48-459d-86f2-bdb131460741","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:02:54.581Z","parentId":"e0939b9a-d9bb-4416-b399-cadb780b776e"}
